value.value: 腎臓肥大
larger than average size of the kidney
上半規管の異常
any structural anomaly of the upper, superior segment of the long bony tube of the labyrinth that is involved in the sense of balance
血管透過性の増加
greater or faster ability of the blood vessels to permit the passage of substances such as fluid, heat, or gases
血管透過性の減少
reduced or slower ability of the blood vessels to permit the passage of substances such as fluid, heat, or gases
中足骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the five bones of the hindpaws/feet that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges
中手骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges
中手骨の欠如
missing all of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges

label.value: abnormal response to CNS ischemic injury

value.value: 中枢神経系（CNS)虚血性外傷（に対する）応答変化

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal response to CNS ischemic injury

value.value: altered response to lack of adequate blood flow, due to trauma or disease, to support the normal functioning of a tissue in the central nervous system

label.value: increased susceptibility to ischemic brain injury

value.value: 虚血性脳外傷に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to ischemic brain injury

value.value: more severe response, such as increased incidence and/or size of necrotic tissue, to lack of adequate blood flow resulting from trauma or disease, to support the normal functioning of all or part of the brain compared to controls
細胞周期の異常
failure to progress or abnormal progression through the stages of the cell cycle
無水晶体
absence of the crystalline lens of the eye

label.value: decreased susceptibility to induced joint inflammation

value.value: 関節炎に対する感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased susceptibility to induced joint inflammation

value.value: reduced or absent inflammatory response in the joints due to chemical or mechanical agents
NK細胞溶解の促進

label.value: increased natural killer cell mediated cytotoxicity

value.value: increased ability of directed killing of a target cell by a natural killer cell through the release of granules containing cytotoxic mediators or through the engagement of death receptors
ヒラメ筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the superficial flat broad muscle of the calf that is responsible for plantar flexion of the foot
腓腹筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the two-headed large muscle of the posterior portion of the lower hindleg, the most superficial of the calf muscles
前頸骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the muscle of the shin that is responsible for dorsiflexion and inversion of the foot
骨格筋線維の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the skeletal muscle fibers, the large multinucleated cells that make up the skeletal muscles
卵筒の形態異常
any structural anomaly in the transient cup-like structure of the epiblast that consists of a single layer of embryonic cells
水脊髄症
increased fluid in the central canal of the spinal cord
尿膜の欠損
missing fetal membrane which contributes to the formation of the umbilical cord and placenta
前パルス抑制の異常
anomaly in the ability of a relatively mild stimulus to suppress the response to a strong, startle-eliciting stimulus
皮膚張力強度の減少
reduction in the normal maximum tension the skin can withstand without tearing
筋前駆細胞移入の異常
defects in the movement of cells that will develop into muscle cells out of the somites and/or to the appropriate location in the body
細胞遊走の異常
any anomaly in the movement of cells from one site to another, often occurring during developmental or chemotactic processes
角膜支質厚みの減少
reduced width of the lamellated connective tissue layer of the cornea
前方角膜実質形態異常
any structural anomaly of the anterior segment of the lamellated connective tissue layer of the cornea
後部角膜実質形態異常
any structural anomaly of the posterior segment of the lamellated connective tissue layer of the cornea
角膜支質発生の異常
anomalous differentiation of the lamellated connective tissue layer of the cornea
角膜光散乱の増大
anomaly in the normal transmission of light through the cornea; light is reflected or absorbed instead; often due to anomalies in the arrangement of lamella in the corneal stroma
腱硬直の異常
altered ability of tendon to maintain tensile strength and load
腱硬直の減少
reduced ability of tendon to maintain tensile strength and load
網膜剥離
part or all of the retinal neural layer is separated from the outer pigmented layer of the retina; may occur with aging or as a result of trauma
近視
optical condition in which only rays from a finite distance from the eye focus on the retina
強い近視
an optical condition involving enlarging of the eye, scleral thinning and frequent detachment of the retina resulting from stress associated with excessive axial elongation
強膜の菲薄化
reduction in the width of the fibrous, outer envelope of the eyeball, the sclera may appear blue as a result of the underlying epithelium showing through
肝臓変性
deterioration of the liver due to injury or disease, often accompanied by loss of function
無頭蓋
complete or partial absence of a skull; usually associated with anencephaly
心房の形態異常
any structural anomaly of one or both of the two upper chambers of the heart, to which the blood returns from the circulation
恐怖関連応答の異常
altered emotional response related to anticipation of specific pain or danger
目新しさへの応答の異常
alteration in amount of exploration/investigation of a novel object, situation or environment
短い頬骨
reduced length of the bone that forms the prominence of the cheek
短い大腿骨
reduced length of the long bone of the thigh
踝短突起の欠如

absence of the short projection extending from the base of the manubrium of the malleus which contacts the upper part of the tympanic membrane where the tympanic cavity makes a deep pocket (epitympanic pocket) surrounding the cartilaginous nodule
核形態の異常

any structural anomaly of a membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated; in most cells, the nucleus contains all of the cell's chromosomes except the organellar chromosomes, and is the site of RNA synthesis and processing, but in some species, or in specialized cell types, RNA metabolism or DNA replication may be absent
副甲状腺の肥大

increased size of the two small, paired endocrine glands, usually found embedded in the connective tissue capsule on the posterior surface of the thyroid gland; they secrete parathyroid hormone (PTH) that regulates calcium and phosphorous metabolism
副甲状腺の矮小化

decreased size of the two small, paired endocrine glands, usually found embedded in the connective tissue capsule on the posterior surface of the thyroid gland; they secrete parathyroid hormone (PTH) that regulates calcium and phosphorous metabolism
色素性副甲状腺

presence of melanocytes and/or melanin in either of the two small, paired endocrine glands, usually found embedded in the connective tissue capsule on the posterior surface of the thyroid gland; they secrete parathyroid hormone (PTH) that regulates calcium and phosphorous metabolism
呼吸器系発達の異常
aberrant differentiation of pulmonary tissues
くる病

overproduction and deficient calcification of osteoid tissue due to vitamin D deficiency; can lead to skeletal deformities, growth defects, hypocalcemia, and sometimes tetany; skeletal fractures occur frequently
消化器系の発達異常
abnormal formation of the organ system that converts ingested food to nutrients and energy
